critique: The document is an executive order issued by President Obama prohibiting the importation of jadeite and rubies mined or extracted from Burma. It invokes the International Emergency Economic Powers Act (IEEPA) and other laws to address a national emergency related to Burma. The order includes exceptions for certain situations, such as goods previously exported from the United States and transactions consistent with international obligations. It also authorizes the Secretary of the Treasury to implement the order and waives certain sanctions under the JADE Act.
